title: Why some Google employees live in parking lots
text:
Why some Google employees live in parking lots 
Times of India Saturday 24th October, 2015 
1. 
Rents are too high Ben Discoe lived at the Google campus for 13 months (October 2011 to November 2012) because the rent in South Bay area was too high. He already had a house payment and alimony to pay, and turns out living in a parking lot is convenient. 
The security team at Google did check up on him when he started living on the campus, but left him to it once they were certain that he was just an eccentric Googler....
